The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	New Delhi: National sports federations (NSF) can no longer avoid public scrutiny with the sports ministry Tuesday bringing them under the ambit of the Right to Information Act (RTI), making it mandatory for these bodies to appoint public information officers and appellate authorities. The government today issued an order asking all the NSFs to immediately designate Central Public Information Officers and Appellate Authorities according to Section five of the RTI Act 2005.        
	London: Chelsea striker Didier Drogba has been handed a two-match European ban after being sent off in the Champions League defeat by Inter Milan at Stamford Bridge earlier this month, Uefa said in a statement on Tuesday.        
	Rome: Italy coach Marcello Lippi has indicated he will step down again after the World Cup in South Africa. Lippi has been linked with a return to the club he formerly coached, Juventus, in a managerial position.        
	Stuttgart: Former Germany goalkeeper Jens Lehmann will retire at the end of this season. I will play my last game on May 8 (when the Bundesliga season ends), the 40-year-old Stuttgart keeper said on Tuesday.         
	London: Former West Indies left-arm seamer Pedro Collins has agreed to play for Middlesex throughout the upcoming English county season. Collins, who has not played international cricket since 2006, will join Middlesex midway through April, having left Surrey in October after two seasons there.        
	Islamabad: The Pakistan Cricket Board is proposing a Test and one-day series against South Africa in the United Arab Emirates this year. PCBs chief operating officer Wasim Bari said on Tuesday that it has asked the Proteas to play three Tests and five ODIs, with the proposal being to start the series from Oct. 28.           
	Johannesburg: Caster Semenya, the 800 metres world champion, will not return to competitive athletics until her gender verification case has been resolved, Athletics South Africa announced on Tuesday.         
	New Delhi: Defending champions India will take on China in their campaign opener at the 19th Sultan Azlan Shah Cup International Hockey Tournament to be held in Ipoh, Malaysia from May 6-16.          
	Belgrade: Former world No.1 Ana Ivanovic has pulled out of Serbias Fed Cup World Group playoff tie with Slovakia next month over poor form.     
